1. Install latest node and npm (package management tool for node):

		sudo apt-get install python-software-properties
		sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/node.js
		sudo apt-get update
		sudo apt-get install nodejs npm

2. Install git:

		sudo apt-get install git

3. Download source code:

		git clone https://github.com/rweigel/datacache.git

4. Install dependencies (described in package.json):
		
		cd datacache
		npm install

5. Run:

		node app.js

	or to keep it running after logout:
		
		screen
		node app.js
		ctrl + A
		ctrl + D

	Later if you want to attach to that screen again:

		screen -r

6. Also nodemon is a handy tool for dev. It watches source code and automatically reload the program (like in Eclipse). If you do:
		
		sudo npm install -g nodemon
		nodemon app.js

any changes to app.js will be automactically loaded and you will never need to restart the server during development. 